{{Infobox organization |name = Bangladesh Petroleum Institute |image = |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = |motto = |formation = 1981 |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = |headquarters = [[Uttara Thana|Uttara]], [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]] |location = |coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> |region_served = Bangladesh |members = |language = Bengali |leader_title = |leader_name = |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [http://www.energysector-bpi.org.bd/ Bangladesh Petroleum Institute] |remarks = }}
'''Bangladesh Petroleum Institute''' or BPI is an autonomous national research institute that carries out research on [[hydrocarbon]] and provide technical assistance to organizations in the petroleum industry and is located in [[Uttara Thana|Uttara]], [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]].<ref name="wer">{{cite web|title=Bangladesh Petroleum Institute|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Bangladesh_Petroleum_Institute|website=en.banglapedia.org|publisher=Banglapedia|accessdate=26 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=BD moots Bapex-Gazprom joint venture to Russia|url=http://archive.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/2016/may/06/bd-moots-bapex-gazprom-joint-venture-russia|website=archive.dhakatribune.com|publisher=Dhaka Tribune|accessdate=26 October 2016}}</ref>
==History== The institute was created on January 1981, it is under the [[Ministry of Power, Energy and Mineral Resources|Ministry of Energy and Mineral Resources]] of Bangladesh.<ref name="wer"></ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Riaz|first1=Ali|last2=Rahman|first2=Mohammad Sajjadur|title=Routledge Handbook of Contemporary Bangladesh|publisher=Routledge|isbn=9781317308775|pages=251|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nC9-CwAAQBAJ&pg=PA251&dq=%22Bangladesh+Petroleum+Institute%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjbiJfE1vjPAhWCcj4KHc80CbgQ6AEIJDAB#v=onepage&q=%22Bangladesh%20Petroleum%20Institute%22&f=false|language=en}}</ref> In 2004 Bangladesh Petroleum Institute act was passed by the parliament which made allocated more resource to skill development in the oil,gas and petroleum industry.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Fund|first1=International Monetary|title=Bangladesh: Poverty Reduction Strategy Paper|publisher=International Monetary Fund|isbn=9781451876642|pages=111|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PvEzTJY7RvoC&pg=PA111&dq=%22Bangladesh+Petroleum+Institute%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjbiJfE1vjPAhWCcj4KHc80CbgQ6AEIKTAC#v=onepage&q=%22Bangladesh%20Petroleum%20Institute%22&f=false|language=en}}</ref>
