'''Gerhard Thielcke'''  (February 14, 1931 [[Köthen (Anhalt)|Köthen, Germany]] – July 22, 2007 [[Radolfzell]], [[Germany]]) was a [[Germany|German]] [[environmentalist]], professor and co-founder of the [[Bund für Umwelt und Naturschutz Deutschland]] (BUND: League for the environment and nature conservation, Germany), an important German environmental organization.

Thielcke died on July 22, 2007 in [[Radolfzell]], [[Germany]].

